7 An Act relating to fireworks; amending 68 O.S. 2021,
Section 1623, which relates to conditions for
8 storage, transportation, sale, and use; updating
statutory language; removing certain requirements to
9 sell fireworks within certain time frame; prohibiting
counties from restricting certain firework display
10 under certain circumstances; and providing an
effective date.
11
12
13 AUTHOR: Add the following House Coauthor: Kendrix
14 AMENDMENT NO. 1. Strike the title, enacting clause, and entire bill
and insert:
15
16 "An Act relating to fireworks; creating the Rocket's
Red Glare Act; amending 68 O.S. 2021, Section 1623,
17 which relates to conditions for storage,
transportation, sale, and use; updating statutory
18 language; removing certain requirements to sell
fireworks within certain time frame; prohibiting
19 counties from restricting certain firework display
under certain circumstances; amending 68 O.S. 2021,
20 Section 1624, as amended by Section 1, Chapter 144,
O.S.L. 2024 (68 O.S. Supp. 2025, Section 1624), which
21 relates to the distribution of skyrockets; removing
the prohibition of certain skyrockets; providing for
22 noncodification; and declaring an emergency.
23
24
ENGR. H. A. to ENGR. S. B. NO. 1948 Page 1

1 BE I T ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
2 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law not to be
3 codified in the Oklahoma Statutes reads as follows:
4 This act shall be known and may be cited as the "Rocket's Red
5 Glare Act".
6 SECTION 2. AMENDATORY 68 O.S. 2021, Section 1623, is
7 amended to read as follows:
8 Section 1623. A. Consumer Fireworks fireworks may be legally
9 stored, transported, sold, and used in this state with the
10 exceptions and conditions specified under the provisions of Section
11 1621 et seq. of this title and consistent with Section 22-110 of
12 Title 11 of the Oklahoma Statutes. Novelties may be legally stored,
13 transported, sold, and used in this state.
14 B. All fireworks storage and sales areas shall be conspicuously
15 posted with signs reading “FIREWORKS-NO SMOKING”.
16 C. Fireworks offered for retail sale must shall be sold
17 according to the National Fire Protection Association (NFPA) 1124
18 Chapter 7, 2006 Edition. Any facility licensed to sell consumer
19 fireworks prior to November 15, 2009, shall be exempt from the NFPA
20 regulations listed in this subsection but shall remain under the
21 regulation of the date of licensure. Mail-order sales to consumers
22 are prohibited through any medium of either interstate or intrastate
23 commerce. Sales of fireworks may only shall be made at properly
24 licensed retail locations within the State of Oklahoma this state.
ENGR. H. A. to ENGR. S. B. NO. 1948 Page 2

1 A sa les clerk must shall be on duty to serve the consumer at the
2 time of purchase.
3 D. An enclosed building used for sale of fireworks to the
4 public shall be built according to the International Building Code
5 (IBC) 2006 Edition and/or or the codes and standards adopted by the
6 Oklahoma Uniform Building Code Commission.
7 E. The retail license holder shall be responsible for the safe
8 operation of retail sales to the public. The retail license holder
9 shall be at least sixteen (16) years of age.
10 F. Fireworks may be sold by licensed manufacturers,
11 distributors, or wholesalers at wholesale or retail and by retailers
12 to residents and nonresidents of the state from January 1 until
13 December 31 of each calendar year. Fireworks may only be sold by
14 licensed retailers from June 15 until July 6 or the first Sunday
15 after July 4th, whichever is later, and from December 15 until
16 January 2 to residents and nonresidents of the state each calendar
17 year.
18 G. Nothing in Section 1621 et seq. of this title shall be
19 construed to require the State Fire Marshal to inspect or cause to
20 be inspected portable retail fireworks stands, tents, or other
21 nonrigid shelters prior to opening; provided, the provisions of this
22 subsection shall not prohibit the local governing authority of the
23 location of the portable retail fireworks stand, tent, or other
24
ENGR. H. A. to ENGR. S. B. NO. 1948 Page 3

1 nonr igid shelter from inspecting such stands, tents, or other
2 nonrigid shelters prior to opening.
3 H. No county shall prohibit a private outdoor consumer
4 fireworks for a noncommercial purpose, provided that:
5 1. Such display is located on private property;
6 2. No county burn ban is in effect as provided for in Section
7 16-26 of Title 2 of the Oklahoma Statutes; and
8 3. There are no red flag fire warnings in effect, meaning:
9 a. no sustained winds greater than twenty (20) miles per
10 hour,
11 b. the relative humidity is above twenty-five percent
12 (25%), and
13 c. the ten-hour dead fuel is above nine percent (9%)
14 moisture.
15 I. Persons lighting fireworks under the conditions listed in
16 paragraph 3 of subsection H of this section shall notify the local
17 responding fire department before lighting any fireworks.
18 SECTION 3. AMENDATORY 68 O.S. 2021, Section 1624, as
19 amended by Section 1, Chapter 144, O.S.L. 2024 (68 O.S. Supp. 2025,
20 Section 1624), is amended to read as follows:
21 A. From and after July 5, 1981, the sale, gift, distribution or
22 use of skyrockets with sticks as defined by the United States
23 Consumer Product Safety Commission is hereby prohibited within the
24 State of Oklahoma. This prohibition shall include, but is not
ENGR. H. A. to ENGR. S. B. NO. 1948 Page 4

1 limi ted to, explosive devices commonly known as "bottle rockets" or
2 "stick rockets". Distribution, gift or sale from Oklahoma to a
3 person outside the State of Oklahoma shall not be considered as
4 occurring within the State of Oklahoma. The provisions of this
5 subsection shall not apply to the sale of skyrockets with sticks by
6 retail and wholesale firework distributors to state-licensed outdoor
7 display operators or the use of skyrockets with sticks in connection
8 with commercial aerial displays performed by state-licensed outdoor
9 display operators.
10 B. Any and all items of Consumer Fireworks not properly labeled
11 according to the United States Consumer Product Safety Commission
12 and identified with the appropriate United States Department of
13 Transportation markings is prohibited under the provisions of
14 Section 1621 et seq. of this title.
15 SECTION 4. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
16 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
17 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
18 be in full force from and after its passage and approval."
